    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>On pages such as <a href="http://framework.zend.com/manual/en/zend.application.core-functionality.html">http://framework.zend.com/manual/en/…</a>
where large tables are used the sidebar (containing the index of ZF class names) overlays the table, making parts of the table unreadable.</p>

<p>This is happening on Safari 3 for Mac, Firefox 3 for Mac, and IE7 Windows. I am sure most browsers are affected.</p>

